<section class="outdoor-page" aria-label="Outdoor furniture by Innate Furniture">
  <div class="outdoor-hero">
    <div class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-hero__grid">
      <div class="outdoor-hero__copy">
        <p class="outdoor-kicker">Outdoor furniture, made in Christchurch</p>
        <h1>Custom outdoor dining tables, built properly</h1>
        <p class="outdoor-lead">Outdoor dining tables, café tables and bar leaners made around your deck, courtyard, venue or patio, with Alfresco porcelain and selected timber options where they make sense.</p>
        <div class="outdoor-actions" aria-label="Outdoor page actions">
          <a class="outdoor-btn outdoor-btn--primary" href="/pages/contact?topic=outdoor-furniture">Enquire about an outdoor dining table</a>
          <a class="outdoor-btn outdoor-btn--quiet" href="#outdoor-products">View outdoor dining tables</a>
        </div>
      </div>
      <figure class="outdoor-hero__image">
        <img src="{{ 'hardwood-outdoor-dining-table-innate-furniture.png' | file_img_url: '1400x' }}" alt="Hardwood outdoor dining table on a timber deck with chairs and planting" width="1480" height="1110" loading="eager" decoding="async">
        <figcaption>
          <span>Custom sizing</span>
          <span>Timber or Alfresco porcelain</span>
          <span>Residential + commercial</span>
        </figcaption>
      </figure>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-evidence" aria-label="Outdoor furniture proof points">
    <article>
      <span>Made to order</span>
      <strong>Custom sizes, outdoor-suitable surfaces and nationwide delivery.</strong>
      <p>Length, width, height, base style and finish are tuned once we understand the space.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span>Material judgement</span>
      <strong>Timber for character. Porcelain for easier cleaning.</strong>
      <p>We are direct about what suits exposed, high-use and hospitality settings.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span>Workshop + local supply</span>
      <strong>Designed & made in Ōtautahi Christchurch</strong>
      <p>Bases, frames and finishes are specified as furniture, not disposable patio décor.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span>Project fit</span>
      <strong>Homes, cafes, and anyone seeking quality</strong>
      <p>Useful for decks, courtyards, entrances, balconies and outdoor dining areas.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-intro">
    <p class="outdoor-kicker">A practical way to choose</p>
    <h2>Start with the setting, then choose the surface.</h2>
    <div class="outdoor-intro__text">
      <p>Exposure, cleaning expectations and seating numbers decide more than style does.</p>
      <p>Once those are clear, the material choice is usually straightforward.</p>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-choice" aria-label="Outdoor material options">
    <article>
      <span class="outdoor-choice__number">01</span>
      <h3>Timber, when warmth matters.</h3>
      <p>Selected outdoor-suitable timbers bring grain and character outside. They still need normal care, so finish, weathering and maintenance are part of the recommendation.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="outdoor-choice__number">02</span>
      <h3>Porcelain when easy care matters</h3>
      <p>Alfresco porcelain, usually paired with steel, suits busy homes, cafés and venues that need easier cleaning and a crisp surface.</p>
    </article>
    <article>
      <span class="outdoor-choice__number">03</span>
      <h3>Custom made for your space</h3>
      <p>Decks, courtyards and venues rarely follow standard dimensions. We adjust size, height, base style and finish around the space.</p>
    </article>
  </div>

  <div class="outdoor-reviews-slot" data-outdoor-reviews-slot></div>

  <div class="outdoor-proof">
    <div class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-proof__panel">
      <div>
        <p class="outdoor-kicker">Built with the same standards as our indoor work</p>
        <h2>Not throwaway outdoor décor.</h2>
      </div>
      <div class="outdoor-proof__body">
        <p>Innate outdoor pieces are approached as proper furniture: clear material choices, durable bases, and finishes chosen for the environment.</p>
        <ul>
          <li>Dining tables, café tables, bar leaners and patio pieces</li>
          <li>Residential, hospitality and commercial projects</li>
          <li>Timber, steel and Alfresco porcelain options</li>
          <li>Made in Christchurch, delivered nationwide</li>
        </ul>
        <p class="outdoor-note">Outdoor timber needs normal care and maintenance. If porcelain is the better fit for your setting, we will say so.</p>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-questions">
    <div class="outdoor-questions__head">
      <p class="outdoor-kicker">Useful answers first</p>
      <h2>Common questions before ordering.</h2>
    </div>
    <div class="outdoor-faq" role="list">
      <details open>
        <summary>Is timber suitable outside?</summary>
        <p>Yes, when the species, finish and exposure make sense. It will still weather and need normal care over time, so we talk through maintenance before recommending it.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>What is easiest to maintain?</summary>
        <p>For most high-use outdoor settings, Alfresco porcelain surfaces with steel bases are the lower-maintenance option.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Can you make a custom size?</summary>
        <p>Yes. Most Innate pieces are made to order, including outdoor tables and leaners.</p>
      </details>
      <details>
        <summary>Do you work with cafés and venues?</summary>
        <p>Yes. We build for homes, hospitality fit-outs and commercial outdoor areas.</p>
      </details>
    </div>
  </div>

  <div id="outdoor-products" class="outdoor-wrap outdoor-products-intro">
    <p class="outdoor-kicker">Outdoor range</p>
    <h2>Choose an outdoor dining table starting point. We’ll tune the details.</h2>
    <p>Browse the outdoor range below. Prices are starting points; final quotes depend on size, surface, base, finish and delivery.</p>
    <ul class="outdoor-product-notes" aria-label="Outdoor product grid notes">
      <li>Made to order from the Christchurch workshop.</li>
      <li>Timber or Alfresco porcelain porcelain depending on the setting.</li>
      <li>Quote confirms size, finish, delivery and inclusions.</li>
    </ul>
    <a class="outdoor-range-link" href="/pages/contact?topic=outdoor-furniture">Enquire about an outdoor dining table</a>
  </div>
</section>

<script>
  document.addEventListener('DOMContentLoaded', function () {
    var outdoorPage = document.querySelector('.outdoor-page');
    if (!outdoorPage) return;

    var reviewSlot = document.querySelector('[data-outdoor-reviews-slot]');
    var reviewSection = document.querySelector('.template-collection.template-sufix-outdoor-furniture .shopify-section.apps');
    if (reviewSlot && reviewSection && !reviewSlot.contains(reviewSection)) {
      reviewSlot.appendChild(reviewSection);
    }

    var productMeta = {
      'alfresco-asterix-dining-table': 'Alfresco porcelain · custom sizing',
      'beech-asterix-outdoor-dining-table': 'Outdoor timber · Asterix base',
      'alfresco-outdoor-dining': 'Alfresco porcelain · made to order',
      'hardwood-dining-table': 'Hardwood top · steel base',
      'alfresco-round-dining-table': 'Round Alfresco porcelain',
      'hardwood-round-dining-table': 'Round hardwood outdoor table',
      'alfresco-bar-leaner': 'Alfresco porcelain · bar height',
      'exterior-bar-leaner': 'Hardwood top · bar height',
      'alfresco-coffee-table': 'Alfresco porcelain · patio setting',
      'exterior-coffee-table': 'Hardwood outdoor coffee table',
      'alfresco-outdoor-bar-stool': 'Alfresco porcelain · steel frame',
      'hardwood-bar-stool': 'Hardwood top · steel frame'
    };

    document.querySelectorAll('a.collection-product[href*="/products/"]').forEach(function (card) {
      if (card.querySelector('.outdoor-product-meta')) return;
      var href = card.getAttribute('href') || '';
      var handle = href.split('/products/')[1];
      if (!handle) return;
      handle = handle.split(/[?#]/)[0];
      var meta = productMeta[handle];
      var title = card.querySelector('.collection-product-title');
      if (meta && title) {
        var node = document.createElement('div');
        node.className = 'outdoor-product-meta';
        node.textContent = meta;
        title.insertAdjacentElement('afterend', node);
      }
    });

    document.querySelectorAll('body *').forEach(function (el) {
      var style = window.getComputedStyle(el);
      if (!style || (style.position !== 'fixed' && style.position !== 'sticky')) return;
      var rect = el.getBoundingClientRect();
      var nearRight = rect.right > window.innerWidth - 92;
      var small = rect.width <= 92 && rect.height <= 92 && rect.width >= 18 && rect.height >= 18;
      var text = ((el.getAttribute('aria-label') || '') + ' ' + (el.getAttribute('title') || '') + ' ' + (el.textContent || '') + ' ' + (el.innerHTML || '')).toLowerCase();
      var looksDocument = text.indexOf('pdf') !== -1 || text.indexOf('document') !== -1 || text.indexOf('download') !== -1 || text.indexOf('print') !== -1;
      if (nearRight && small && looksDocument) {
        el.setAttribute('hidden', 'hidden');
        el.style.setProperty('display', 'none', 'important');
      }
    });
  });
</script>
